title: Diagnostics regression in rustc?

labels.name: A-diagnostics
labels.description: Area: Messages for errors, warnings, and lints

body:
https://www.reddit.com/r/rust/comments/2mwloh/hashmap_does_not_implement_contains_key/

Using a previous nightly (didn't think to note the version) I got extensive diagnostics messages pointing to exactly what the issue was:

```
test.rs:9:36: 9:40 error: mismatched types: expected `&T`, found `T` (expected &-ptr, found type parameter)
test.rs:9         if ! self.map.contains_key(node) {
                                             ^~~~
test.rs:9:14: 9:41 error: the trait `core::cmp::Eq` is not implemented for the type `T`
test.rs:9         if ! self.map.contains_key(node) {
                       ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
test.rs:9:14: 9:41 error: the trait `collections::hash::Hash` is not implemented for the type `T`
test.rs:9         if ! self.map.contains_key(node) {
                       ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
test.rs:10:13: 10:50 error: the trait `core::cmp::Eq` is not implemented for the type `T`
test.rs:10             self.map.insert(node, HashSet::new());
                       ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
test.rs:10:13: 10:50 error: the trait `collections::hash::Hash` is not implemented for the type `T`
test.rs:10             self.map.insert(node, HashSet::new());
                       ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
test.rs:10:35: 10:47 error: the trait `core::cmp::Eq` is not implemented for the type `T`
test.rs:10             self.map.insert(node, HashSet::new());
                                             ^~~~~~~~~~~~
test.rs:10:35: 10:47 error: the trait `collections::hash::Hash` is not implemented for the type `T`
test.rs:10             self.map.insert(node, HashSet::new());
                                             ^~~~~~~~~~~~
```

but after updating to the latest _rustc 0.13.0-nightly (399ff259e 2014-11-20 00:27:07 +0000)_ I get the significantly less informative messages quoted by the author:

```
test.rs:9:23: 9:42 error: type `std::collections::hash::map::HashMap<T, std::collections::hash::set::HashSet<T>>` does not implement any method in scope named `contains_key`
test.rs:9         if ! self.map.contains_key(&node) {
                                ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
test.rs:10:22: 10:50 error: type `std::collections::hash::map::HashMap<T, std::collections::hash::set::HashSet<T>>` does not implement any method in scope named `insert`
test.rs:10             self.map.insert(node, HashSet::new());
                                ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
```

Is that normal?
